releases.description:
## Fixed

- **Every action-section row is now actionable.** A disabled plugin whose settings already match the store (✓ identical) had no enable control — the third appearance of the same gap (install-only 0.24.0, enable-only 0.27.0, update-only 0.27.1). The rule is now structural: in "Not installed / Disabled / Outdated on this device", every row stages except encrypted-locked ones — the section's action (install / enable / update) is the payload, whether or not the settings transfer happens to be empty. Newly covered cells:
  - disabled + identical → "identical to the store — applying just turns the plugin on" with ⏻ Enable;
  - not-installed + identical (leftover settings matching the store) → the install ladder;
  - outdated + no settings → "no settings anywhere — updates the plugin only";
  - and any state action with no store data runs action-only instead of tripping the missing-store-data error.
